text: Pinus krempfii, or Krempf's pine, is a rare species of pine, endemic to the central highlands of Vietnam in the Da Lat-Nha Trang area. It is unusual in that it has flat needles. Because of this anomaly, it is put in its own subsection, the Krempfianae. ==References== Krempfii Category:Endemic flora of Vietnam Category:Trees of Vietnam Category:Vulnerable flora of Asia
